There are four good numbers in the range [1, 10] : 2, 5, 6, 9.\\nNote that 1 and 1...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"788. Rotated Digits - Leetcode Solution\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.algomap.io/question-bank/rotated-digits\",\n      \"description\": \"If at least one digit is a \\\"changing\\\" digit (<beginning of the code>2, 5, 6, 9<end of the code> ), mark the number as \\\"good\\\".\\nCount Good Numbers:\\nKeep a counter for all numbers that are \\\"good\\\" as per the rules above.\\nOptimization:\\nFor large <beginning of the code>N<end of the code>, we can use a DP array where <beginning of the code>dp...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Rotated Digits\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.simplyleet.com/rotated-digits\",\n      \"description\": \"Only digits 0, 1, 8 remain unchanged, while 2, 5 and 6, 9 swap with each other; digits 3, 4, and...\\nA mapping is used to convert each digit to its rotated counterpart. If a digit is not present in the mapping (i.e., it is 3, 4, or 7), the number is discarded immediately. If the rotated number differs from the original, the number is counted as \\\"good\\\". \",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"张国明/leetcode\",\n      \"url\": \"https://gitee.com/guomingzhang2008/leetcode/blob/main/solution/0700-0799/0788.Rotated%20Digits/README.md\",\n      \"description\": \"limit) {             dp[pos][ok] = ans;         }         return ans;     } };\\nGo\\nfunc rotatedDigits(n int) int { \\td := []int{0, 1, 5, -1, -1, 2, 9, -1, 8, 6} \\tcheck := func(x int) bool { \\t\\ty, t := 0, x \\t\\tk := 1 \\t\\tfor ; t > 0; t...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Solutions\",\n      \"url\": \"https://neetcode.io/solutions/confusing-number\",\n      \"description\": \"Create a mapping of valid digits to their rotated counterparts: <beginning of the code>0->0<end of the code>, <beginning of the code>1->1<end o